  <p align="center"><strong><font size="+2">Board &amp; MLT Retreat</font></strong></p>
  <p>The Board and MLT of Incedo met recently; talking, praying, laughing, assessing, dreaming, questioning, eating, wrestling with issues, visioning, engaging.......... </p>
  <p>Incedo has reached a point on our journey where change has happened, systems have been created, a new culture is forming and people are feeling comfortable, settled in our Missional Community.</p>
  <p><em>Brilliant</em> yet also challenging!</p>
  <p>Barbara Jordan, an American civil rights activist and first African-American Senator in Texas said: </p>
  <p align="center"><em>&ldquo;We are a party of innovation. We do not reject our traditions, 
    but we are willing to adapt to changing circumstances, when change we must. <br>
    We are willing to suffer the discomfort of change in order to achieve a better future.&rdquo;</em></p>
  <p>The Board and MLT see&rsquo;s the need for us to continue to suffer the discomfort of change as we build our evolving Jesus community called Incedo. We must all be comfortable in the discomfort of the journey. Personally, we must all be open to adapt to changing circumstances, something that Incedo gives us all the freedom to explore.</p>
  <p align="center"><strong><font size="+2">Incedo ..... WHY?</font></strong></p>
  <p>We asked the question ... <strong>WHY</strong> does Incedo exist? We came up with these titles:</p>
  <blockquote>
    <blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        <p> People &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Community</p>
        <p> Belonging &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Jesus</p>
        <p> Service &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Freedom</p>
        <p> Explorers &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pioneers<br>
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </blockquote>
  </blockquote>  <p>We asked the <strong>WHY</strong> question and created these sentences:</p>
  <p align="center"><em>A community where we have freedom to explore Jesus and love and serve him</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>Journeying alongside young people and sharing Jesus - Missional community -<br>
    Freedom to respond</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>Love God, Love people, nothing else matters</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>Because we&rsquo;re on a journey that&rsquo;s values based - Jesus Centred, People Focused......</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>A place to put handles on my faith. To love God and love others</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>The freedom to follow Jesus, serve Him and journey alongside others</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>People need to know they can meet Jesus where they&rsquo;re at</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>A vehicle, tool, to love God and love people</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>To be with Jesus where we find Him</em></p>
  <p align="center"><em>Acceptance and valued</em></p>
