  </p>
  <p align="center"><strong><font size="+2">&ldquo;Sitting comfortable in the grey&rdquo;</font></strong></p>
  <p> <img width="552" height="221" src="http://www.incedo.org.nz/Private/Email/Updates/20110330/comfortableinthegrey.jpg"><br>
    <br>
    This phrase came up during our conversations:<br>
      <br>
      How comfortable are we as a Jesus centred people sitting comfortable in the grey?</p>
  <p>Do we feel okay not having/needing all the answers?</p>
  <p>Being comfortable with theological questions where the answer isn't clear?</p>
  <p>It's not so much about the issues, but more about our attitudes?</p>
  <p>What do you think?</p>
  <p align="center"><strong><font size="+2">Scripture</font></strong></p>
  <p>We spent time reflecting in the two passages of scripture below. You may like to take time to carry out your own Lectio Divina on each separate passage, reflecting on them from your perspective as a member of our community.</p>
  <p align="center">John 3:10-21</p>
  <p align="center">Ephesians 2:14-22<br>
  </p>
  <p align="center"><strong><font size="+2">Conclusion</font></strong></p>
  <p>We hope that this update has given you some insight into where the Board and MLT are going and the challenges and opportunities we see in the coming days for Incedo, for you!</p>
  <p>Remember what Barbara Jordan said:</p>
  <p align="center"><em>&ldquo;we are willing to adapt to changing circumstances, when change we must. <br>
  We are willing to suffer the discomfort of change in order to achieve a better future.&rdquo;</em></p>
  <p>Constantly changing, adapting and growing is what is needed from us all. Yes it will be uncomfortable, yes it will be painful, yes it may even lose you some support money. But we are all in this community together, in this community that gives each of us the freedom to explore what it means to follow Jesus together, pioneering new expressions of Faith together. Growing and blossoming together into what God has for us all.</p>
